Vir persone wat nie die diens kan bywoon nie, sal dit aanlyn op me. Bezuidenhout se Facebookblad uitgesaai word. Me. Bezuidenhout, die eienaar van Bezuidenhout Loodgieters, is op 3 Junie in die Netcare Cuyler Hospitaal in Uitenhage oorlede. Sy het in die Kaap by ’n vriendin gaan kuier om haar 60ste verjaardag te vier en is daarna na haar niggie in die Wes Kaap. Me. Bezuidenhout het skielik siek geword en is in die hospitaal opgeneem, waar sy positief vir die Covid-19 virus getoets het. Die oomblik toe haar toestand agteruit gaan, het die hospitaal haar kinders in kennis gestel, waarop hulle almal soontoe gevlieg het. Hulle is toegelaat om tot laat die aand voor haar dood by haar te kuier. Sy is deur haar gesin as ’n ystervrou en dinamiese mens wat baie vir ander mense gedoen het.    Do you have a news lead? Contact our editorial office on 013 243 1434 or our standby number for emergencies on 072 248 3855 to share your story with us. Follow us on the Middelburg Observer Facebook group or page or send a WhatsApp to 072 248 3855 with the words “add me” for the latest news. Notice: Coronavirus reporting at Caxton Local Media aims to combat fake news Dear reader, As your local news provider, we have the duty of keeping you factually informed on Covid-19 developments. As you may have noticed, mis- and disinformation (also known as “fake news”) is circulating online. Caxton Local Media is determined to filter through the masses of information doing the rounds and to separate truth from untruth in order to keep you adequately informed. Local newsrooms follow a strict pre-publication fact-checking protocol. A national task team has been established to assist in bringing you credible news reports on Covid-19. Readers with any comments or queries may contact National Group Editor Irma Green (irma@caxton.co.za) or Legal Adviser Helene Eloff (helene@caxton.co.za).